<h3>js2-mode error highlight problem</h3>

<figure>
<img src='i/emacs_js2-mode_syntax_error_highlight_problem_2016-12-15.png' alt='emacs js2 mode syntax error highlight problem 2016 12 15' width='709' height='695'/>
<figcaption>emacs js2 mode syntax error highlight problem 2016-12-15</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>js2-mode got this annoying syntax error highlight problem.</p>

<p>it sticks with the old school style of requiring semicolon. But thousands packages on npm follows new school style of no semicolon.</p>

<p>〔➤see <a href='http://xahlee.info/js/js_semicolon.html'>JavaScript: Semicolon Rules</a>〕</p>

<p>if you want js2-mode features, a solution is the derivative js3-mode.</p>

</div>
 